body:
This commit adds a transformation from table lookup implemented as mux chains into case statement, such as:
```
mux(key==1 a_0, mux(key==10, a_1, mux(key==25, ...., mux(key==100, a_20, default)...)
```
into:
```
reg GEN; 
case (key)
  1:  GEN <= a_0;
  10:  GEN <= a_1;
  25:  GEN <= a_2
  ...
```

I intentionally didn't implement this transformation in comb canonicalizer since
it create a case operation in SV dialect. Changed LOC is a bit large but it is mostly refactoring 
related to `getLinearMuxChainsComparison`.

Example:
```scala
circuit TableLookup: 
  module TableLookup:
    input t : UInt<5>[6]
    input default : UInt<5>
    input key : UInt<5>
    output v : UInt<5>
    node v1 =  mux(eq(key, UInt<5>("h3")), t[0], default);
    node v2 =  mux(eq(key, UInt<5>("h10")), t[1], v1);
    node v3 =  mux(eq(key, UInt<5>("h12")), t[2], v2);
    node v4 =  mux(eq(key, UInt<5>("h13")), t[3], v3);
    node v5 =  mux(eq(key, UInt<5>("h17")), t[4], v4);
    node v6 =  mux(eq(key, UInt<5>("h18")), t[5], v5);
    v <= v6
```
`firtool -disable-name-preservation` will generate
```verilog
  reg [4:0] _GEN;
  always_comb begin
    priority case (key)
      5'b11000:
        _GEN = t_5;
      5'b10111:
        _GEN = t_4;
      5'b10011:
        _GEN = t_3;
      5'b10010:
        _GEN = t_2;
      5'b10000:
        _GEN = t_1;
      5'b00011:
        _GEN = t_0;
      default:
        _GEN = default_0;
    endcase
  end // always_comb
  assign v = _GEN;
```
